{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":1,"title":"The Current Financial System","iconName":"money","bgColor":"majorelle-blue","imageBgColor":"majorelle-blue-lighter","bottomLinks":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/76be0/money-with-bg.png","srcSet":"/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/62b8c/money-with-bg.png 672w,\n/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/e7748/money-with-bg.png 1344w,\n/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/76be0/money-with-bg.png 2688w","sizes":"(min-width: 2688px) 2688px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/4e936/money-with-bg.webp 672w,\n/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/b1b34/money-with-bg.webp 1344w,\n/static/4d3a29c35d9db186ae107e6e1bd55157/84315/money-with-bg.webp 2688w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 2688px) 2688px, 100vw"}]},"width":2688,"height":2208}}}},"html":"<p>Our current financial system is mainly debt-based which means that digital payments are simply transfers of claims between financial institutions.</p>\n<p>Such transfers have shown to be efficient and practical payment methods. Nonetheless, unbanked and underbanked people can’t join this system as many of them do not have a government-issued ID and/or money.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":2,"title":"Cryptocurrencies","iconName":"bitcoin","bgColor":"dark-green","imageBgColor":"aquamarine-green","bottomLinks":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/fa8f5/blockchain-with-bg.png","srcSet":"/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/24889/blockchain-with-bg.png 516w,\n/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/449e1/blockchain-with-bg.png 1032w,\n/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/fa8f5/blockchain-with-bg.png 2064w","sizes":"(min-width: 2064px) 2064px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/dc0d7/blockchain-with-bg.webp 516w,\n/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/f3759/blockchain-with-bg.webp 1032w,\n/static/51760b415effca2072e62c35f118adbb/93c3e/blockchain-with-bg.webp 2064w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 2064px) 2064px, 100vw"}]},"width":2064,"height":1656}}}},"html":"<p>Cryptocurrencies also tried to solve this problem by making use of a decentralised infrastructure which does not rely on the actions of banks or a monetary authority.</p>\n<p>However, after more than 10 years of existence, we see that cryptocurrencies rely heavily on the very system they were originally intended to provide an alternative to.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":3,"title":"The Trustlines Network","iconName":"trustline","bgColor":"coral-red","imageBgColor":"coral-red-lightest","bottomLinks":[{"link":"https://docs.trustlines.network/resources/wp_content/how_trustlines_works/","label":"Read more about how Trustlines works"}],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/97237/network-with-bg.png","srcSet":"/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/ada53/network-with-bg.png 503w,\n/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/07877/network-with-bg.png 1006w,\n/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/97237/network-with-bg.png 2012w","sizes":"(min-width: 2012px) 2012px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/a33bf/network-with-bg.webp 503w,\n/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/341c4/network-with-bg.webp 1006w,\n/static/79748bb595feecae22356cdcce7965cf/afad0/network-with-bg.webp 2012w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 2012px) 2012px, 100vw"}]},"width":2012,"height":1851}}}},"html":"<p>To combat this issue, why not combine the technological innovation of cryptocurrencies with the benefits of a debt-based financial system?</p>\n<p>This way we reworked the idea to create a fully decentralised, debt-based money creation system using trustless infrastructure. We’ve called it People Powered Money as it is truly inclusive and allows anyone to create their own money, as well as access digital payments and credit.</p>"}}]}}}